[1]
Date: Tue 10 Jan 2006
From: A-Lan Banks <Shabjah@aol.com>
Source: Reuters Foundation AlertNet, Tue 10 Jan 2006 [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/L10554255.htm>

New Human Case of Avian Influenza Confirmed in Sivas Province
-------------------------------------------------------------
Turkey has confirmed a new case of avian influenza in a patient in
the central province of Sivas, the CNN Turk television channel
reported on Tuesday [10 Jan 2006]. The Turkish authorities said on
Monday [9 Jan 2006] that 14 people had been confirmed with bird
flu infections so far. Of these, 3 children died in rural eastern
Turkey last week -- the first deaths from bird flu on the fringes of
Europe. The new case of bird flu in Turkey is one of 8 patients being
tested in Sivas.
Turkey is testing dozens more people elsewhere. The U.N. World Health
Organisation said the victims appeared to have caught the H5N1 bird
flu virus directly from infected birds, as has been happening in
southeast Asia, and not from other people.
